1
00:00:33,310 --> 00:00:34,430
The vegetables were ruined,

2
00:00:35,770 --> 00:00:36,960
and we didn't get any money.

3
00:00:38,650 --> 00:00:40,018
But judging by the look on your face,

4
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,313
it seems you did gain something.

5
00:00:44,310 --> 00:00:46,676
Oh... or could it be...

6
00:00:47,550 --> 00:00:48,812
you went to see someone?

7
00:00:50,203 --> 00:00:50,960
Nothing.

8
00:00:51,930 --> 00:00:54,209
Ah... the quieter you are,

9
00:00:55,330 --> 00:00:56,756
the more suspicious I get.

10
00:01:00,006 --> 00:01:02,000
Hurry up! Or we won't make it in time to apply!

11
00:01:06,210 --> 00:01:10,480
I heard Luang Witsanu is recruiting new soldiers.

12
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:12,320
The pay is good,

13
00:01:12,860 --> 00:01:14,301
and it offers solid security.

14
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:17,704
With your skills,

15
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:21,236
if you were a man, life would be a whole lot easier.

16
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:26,393
Easier?

17
00:02:00,130 --> 00:02:00,880
Rinkham,

18
00:02:01,530 --> 00:02:02,732
where have you been?

19
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,360
I just went out for a walk.

20
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,400
Things are unsettled these days.

21
00:02:12,940 --> 00:02:14,393
Do you truly think it is safe?

22
00:02:15,620 --> 00:02:16,787
I am sorry.

23
00:02:17,384 --> 00:02:19,380
Please do not be angry with me, Dad.

24
00:02:20,970 --> 00:02:25,175
Next time, I will not go anywhere alone.

25
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:31,427
You are always like this.

26
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,867
I'm truly being careful.

27
00:02:37,570 --> 00:02:39,630
Go get some rest now.

28
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:51,280
Jasmine-scented water...

29
00:02:54,110 --> 00:02:54,916
If this...

30
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:56,633
Don’t speak.

31
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,147
If you smell this strongly of jasmine,

32
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,313
they will surely catch your scent.

33
00:03:12,650 --> 00:03:15,710
Yes, jasmine-scented water.

34
00:03:15,729 --> 00:03:16,818
Would you like some?

35
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,024
See you.

36
00:03:38,049 --> 00:03:38,529
Yes	

37
00:03:47,050 --> 00:03:52,523
I hope fate will bring us together again.

38
00:04:06,330 --> 00:04:07,138
Dad!!

39
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:08,923
Dad!

40
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:10,652
Dad!

41
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:12,338
Dad, what’s wrong with you?

42
00:04:13,450 --> 00:04:15,046
Dad, wake up, Dad!

43
00:04:15,083 --> 00:04:16,867
Dad! Dad! Help!

44
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,507
Help me, Dad!

45
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:20,726
What happened?

46
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:22,363
I don't know.

47
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,646
When I came in, Dad had already collapsed.

48
00:04:25,590 --> 00:04:26,350
Dad...

49
00:04:26,590 --> 00:04:27,329
Dad, please.

50
00:04:27,655 --> 00:04:28,344
Dad...

51
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:31,858
Dad...

52
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:32,984
Dad...

53
00:04:42,530 --> 00:04:43,569
Your medicine has run out.

54
00:04:46,289 --> 00:04:48,280
Do you want to borrow some money from me to buy the medicine first?

55
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:50,553
I have a little bit to spare.

56
00:04:53,778 --> 00:04:54,572
It’s alright.

57
00:04:56,020 --> 00:05:00,344
I think I know what kind of work I need to do now

58
00:05:02,375 --> 00:05:04,030
to get the money to treat my dad.

59
00:05:08,330 --> 00:05:15,273
But, you must take care of my dad while I’m away.

60
00:05:17,427 --> 00:05:19,420
What kind of work is it, Kaewket?

61
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,021
I am sorry,

62
00:06:15,409 --> 00:06:17,400
but I cannot remain honest as my dad taught me to be.

63
00:06:18,990 --> 00:06:21,501
I only need to find some money to treat my dad's illness.

64
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:24,350
Are you truly going?

65
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,680
If anyone catches you,

66
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,116
you will be punished.

67
00:06:31,630 --> 00:06:35,175
But it is the only way I can save my dad.

68
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:47,286
Please look after him for me, Ming.

69
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:29,815
I knew it, I caught your scent.

70
00:07:32,550 --> 00:07:33,384
The scent of jasmine,

71
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:35,784
I still remember it.

72
00:07:36,861 --> 00:07:37,987
You…

73
00:07:38,043 --> 00:07:39,193
What are you doing here?

74
00:07:40,610 --> 00:07:41,864
I came to enlist in the army.

75
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:49,895
In that case... I will help you.

76
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,473
Your shoulders aren’t broad,

77
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:11,329
and your voice isn't deep.

78
00:08:12,410 --> 00:08:13,636
Do you really think they will accept you?

79
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:19,132
Your face looks so tense.

80
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:20,972
Go wash up a bit.

81
00:09:00,570 --> 00:09:03,513
Here, you look much better.

82
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:19,421
This is yours.

83
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,236
You kept it for me,

84
00:09:24,806 --> 00:09:26,800
I thought I had lost it.

85
00:09:28,290 --> 00:09:32,603
It was torn, so I mended it before bringing it back to return to you.

86
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:38,966
You wished to see me again, didn’t you?

87
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:47,575
Since you mended it with the intention of returning it to me...

88
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:50,609
You wished to see me again, didn’t you?

89
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:54,830
I was only teasing.

90
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:59,686
You look as though you are about to be arrested by the authorities.

91
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:18,849
See? Being with me means you don’t have to wait in line.

92
00:10:20,710 --> 00:10:24,307
Is it really alright to cut in front of others like this?

93
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:28,036
It’s fine. Everyone here knows me.

94
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,726
Well, everyone except you, it seems.

95
00:10:31,610 --> 00:10:33,298
Just who exactly are you?

96
00:10:35,710 --> 00:10:38,720
Can someone this small even be a soldier?

97
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:49,187
That is the young lady, the daughter of Luang Wisanu.

98
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:51,655
My apologies, I didn’t see you.

99
00:10:54,770 --> 00:10:57,083
Don't tell me...

100
00:10:57,980 --> 00:10:58,935
you are the daughter of...

101
00:10:58,972 --> 00:10:59,803
Rinkham!

102
00:11:00,338 --> 00:11:02,330
Where have you been idling away your time again?
